# Modern UI (shadcn)

## Stack

- Use **shadcn/ui** primitives from `@/components/ui/*` (Base UI + Nova preset). Add new primitives with `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`.
- Use **`cn()`** from `@/lib/utils` to merge Tailwind classes.
- Theme tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` (CSS variables). Prefer semantic classes: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, `text-primary`, etc.

## Layout and composition

- **Route-specific UI** stays next to the route under `src/app/.../<route>/components/`.
- **Shared / cross-route UI** goes in `src/components/` (`layout/`, `providers/`, etc.).
- Prefer **Card** (`CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter`) for grouped content, forms on marketing pages, and dashboard panels.

## Interaction and density

- Use **Button** variants: `default`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `destructive`, `link`; sizes include `sm`, `default`, `lg`, `icon-*`.
- Pair **Label** + **Input** / **Textarea** for forms; show errors with `text-destructive`.
- **Do not** call `buttonVariants()` or import from `"use client"` UI modules inside **Server Components** — either mark the parent as `"use client"` or use static `className` strings / compose a small client child.

## Theming

- **next-themes** is wired in `AppProviders` (`attribute="class"`). User-facing chrome may include **ModeToggle** where appropriate.
- Avoid hard-coded grays; use `muted`, `border`, `accent`, and sidebar tokens for dashboard chrome.

## Polish

- Prefer **consistent spacing** (`gap-*`, `space-y-*`), **rounded-xl** cards, subtle **ring-1 ring-border/60** or **shadow-sm** / **shadow-lg** on elevated surfaces.
- Keep **accessible** labels, focus rings (built into shadcn controls), and semantic headings.
